{"type":"spell","name":"Heights of the Great Tower","system":{"technique":{"value":"cr"},"form":{"value":"te"},"baseLevel":3,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"targetSize":7,"complexity":3,"ritual":true,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This ritual conjures four fully-formed levels of the Great Tower, each 20 feet in height and building directly onto the level below, adding 80 feet to the tower in an instant. As with conjuring the foundations, this ritual requires an Int + Finesse stress roll against an Ease Factor of 12. A failed Finesse roll creates a section of tower of shoddy quality, while a successful roll creates a standard quality section. Botch dice on this Finesse roll are equal to 1 + 1 for each other level where the magus failed to meet the Finesse roll (failures should be recorded for future reference). This represents the inherent complexities and dangers of the project.\nBotches on this roll should be handled as story events, but clearly a botch in creating and assembling several thousand tons of stone is going to be significant. As the tower grows, the complexity of controlling the magic also grows, as does the risk of disaster, which may act as a limiting factor on the number of levels a magus would feel safe in conjuring.\nNote that by increasing the level of this spell by one magnitude, 40 levels of the tower could be produced, and 400 levels could be produced by increasing the spell by two magnitudes. But doing so should have a direct impact on the number of botch dice for the required Finesse roll. For each additional magnitude of size, add +3 to both the botch dice and the Finesse roll Ease Factor.\nCasting this spell creates a preternatural tether of 1 and adds +1 to the aura variation modifier.","source":"HP","page":40,"indexKey":"heights-of-the-great-tower","enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/te.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266623057,"modifiedTime":1730266623057,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"04KdszwF3pA2WpBs","folder":"Cy6JvysNx2CNSwuF","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Extinguish the Abhorrent Flame","system":{"technique":{"value":"pe"},"form":{"value":"ig"},"baseLevel":4,"range":{"value":"sight"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell instantly extinguishes any individual fire up to the size of a campfire. The extinguished fire can be relit by mundane or magical means, but does not relight by itself.\nTo feel comfortable, Tolides shuns the heat and light of fires almost as much as he avoids sunlight, and he uses this spell to extinguish flames even from afar. It also comes in handy for affecting the sources of light of those who depend on flames to see in the dark.","source":"MoH","page":132,"indexKey":"extinguish-the-abhorrent-flame","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/ig.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266564295,"modifiedTime":1730266564295,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"053IrZA8KjgoybTC","folder":"TXWRpVwDyXc4LXyP","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Teeth of the Earth Mother","system":{"technique":{"value":"mu"},"form":{"value":"te"},"baseLevel":3,"range":{"value":"voice"},"duration":{"value":"sun"},"target":{"value":"group"},"complexity":2,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"You cause twenty pointed pillars of white marble to spring up from the ground to a height of 12 feet, forming a circle 3 paces in diameter. At their tops, the pillars are thin and as sharp as spears. At the base, where they touch, they are 18 inches thick. When the pillars spring up, they can be used to cage people, to form a wall, or simply to skewer enemies. Climbing to the top of the pillars requires three Athletics stress rolls against an Ease Factor of 12, and the tops break away when the target reaches them, causing the victim to fall. Skewering a target does +25 damage, possibly more on following rounds if the victim struggles or is exceptionally heavy. When the spell ends, the pillars crumble to dust.","source":"ArM5","page":154,"indexKey":"teeth-of-the-earth-mother","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/te.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266623057,"modifiedTime":1730266623057,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"055YGUWmQowFFQVn","folder":"Cy6JvysNx2CNSwuF","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Fog of Confusion","system":{"technique":{"value":"mu"},"form":{"value":"au"},"baseLevel":2,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"year"},"target":{"value":"bound"},"targetSize":4,"complexity":0,"enhancingRequisite":2,"ritual":true,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":true},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":true,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"Turns a bank of fog up to six miles across into a silvery mist too thick to see through. Random screams, thumps, hisses, and other noises harass and confuse anyone within the fog, perhaps even leading them into danger. People have extreme difficulty navigating through the fog, especially through unknown territory. No more than seven people, who must be present at the ritual, can see normally through the fog. The fog does not dissipate until the spell expires.","source":"ArM5","page":128,"indexKey":"fog-of-confusion","general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/au.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730239712993,"modifiedTime":1730239814316,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"eh6ejLC7eDZ9R8Pp","_id":"0EANYMutFLx5cbpb","sort":2300000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Beast of Minuscule Proportions","system":{"technique":{"value":"mu"},"form":{"value":"an"},"baseLevel":4,"range":{"value":"voice"},"duration":{"value":"sun"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"<p lang=\"en-US\" style=\"line-height: 100%; margin-top: 0.21cm; margin-bottom: 0cm\">Reduces the size of an animal by 2. This modifies Strength by –4, reduces the range for each wound type by two points, and increases Quickness by +2. The beast appears to be the runt of its litter, unfit to live.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"beast-of-minuscule-proportions","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"Yves Stadler"},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/an.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":"Compendium.world.spells-animal.Item.0LKbTW9klh3HCZpS","duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.3","createdTime":1729689989096,"modifiedTime":1729689989096,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"0LKbTW9klh3HCZpS","ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3},"folder":"Wzb8TRtvqtVwjohA","sort":0}
{"type":"spell","name":"The Riches That are Rightfully Mine(d)","system":{"technique":{"value":"cr"},"form":{"value":"te"},"baseLevel":15,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"group"},"complexity":1,"ritual":true,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell fills a large chest or other sturdy container with silver pennies equal to about 650 Mythic Pounds. The magus may choose the imprint on the coins, but this mark always bears some trace of the magus’s sigil, which does tend to make them traceable.\nA copy of this spell resides at the Great Library of Durenmar, but it is infamous for causing inflationary troubles. Given the recent rulings in many Tribunals, a covenant of ten magi would only be permitted to distribute 20 pounds of such silver per year, so that it would take 30 years to exhaust the silver created by even a single casting of the spell. Therefore, while there is nothing to stop a magus from learning this spell in the Great Library, he would surely earn the instant suspicion and attention of the Quaesitores if he did so.","source":"Cov","page":61,"indexKey":"the-riches-that-are-rightfully-mined","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/te.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266623057,"modifiedTime":1730266623057,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"0PildbQprJO5Jeex","folder":"Cy6JvysNx2CNSwuF","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Guttering of the Home-Fires","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"vi"},"baseLevel":1,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"diam"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell temporarily suppresses an Aegis of the Hearth effect. The Aegis of the Hearth effect must be less than half the level of this spell + 3 magnitudes. The known Lab Texts of this spell incorporate a side effect: while the Aegis of the Hearth is lowered, the temperature within the affected boundary is lowered slightly, which sensitive characters might notice.\nThis spell must penetrate the Aegis of the Hearth effect, of course.\nNote that if the Aegis of the Hearth is of a high level, then this spell may need to be a ritual.","source":"HP","page":94,"indexKey":"guttering-of-the-home-fires","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/vi.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266633698,"modifiedTime":1730266633698,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"0Ry0fPVbKQAmHdTw","folder":"FLOveJlX4MXFkepb","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Doublet of Impenetrable Silk","system":{"technique":{"value":"mu"},"form":{"value":"an"},"baseLevel":4,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"sun"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"<p lang=\"en-US\" style=\"line-height: 100%; margin-top: 0.21cm; margin-bottom: 0cm\">Change an item made of animal material — silk, wool, or leather — so it cannot be cut or penetrated by weapons. A simple cloth doublet becomes the equivalent of armor with no Load and a +3 Soak bonus. Armor made of quilted material or any kind of leather improves its Protection by an additional +3. The magic does not make the armor better at absorbing shock, so this +3 bonus is the limit that can be bestowed without changing the material into something completely different. At the storyguide's option, the bonus given by this spell may not apply against strictly blunt weapons like clubs and staves.</p>","source":"ArM5Def","page":0,"indexKey":"doublet-of-impenetrable-silk","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"Yves Stadler"},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/an.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":"Compendium.world.spells-animal.Item.0TR0tXbda21tzPdN","duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.3","createdTime":1729689989096,"modifiedTime":1729689989096,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"0TR0tXbda21tzPdN","ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3},"folder":"Wzb8TRtvqtVwjohA","sort":0}
{"type":"spell","name":"Division According to Blood","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"co"},"baseLevel":10,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"part"},"complexity":0,"enhancingRequisite":1,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":true,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"To cast this spell, the caster holds a glass phial in each hand. One phial contains blood which may come from a mixture of sources. The other phial is empty. Upon casting the spell, all the blood from one individual only (in the first phial) is instantly transported into the second phial. By repeatedly casting this spell (and having a sufficient quantity of empty phials available), the caster may separate out the blood from a number of individuals. If the first phial contains only blood from one individual, then all of it will instantly transport into the second phial.\nThe Intellego requisite is required to distinguish between the different sorts of blood in the phial. The target is Part because only a fraction of the blood (that belonging to one individual) is instantly transported into the second phial.","source":"HP","page":88,"indexKey":"division-according-to-blood","targetSize":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/co.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730240398532,"modifiedTime":1730240398532,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"0VGplHeHU9mqmHmn","folder":"G2cgv5WjMszSYrBJ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Mercury’s Winged Sandals","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"co"},"baseLevel":15,"range":{"value":"personal"},"duration":{"value":"conc"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"The caster can fly. He must make an Intelligence + Finesse roll to change direction or speed; with an Ease Factor related to his current speed — Ease Factor 3 for walking pace, Ease Factor 9 at moderate speed, Ease Factor 12 at maximum speed.\nHe can move at a maximum speed as fast as a running horse — about forty miles an hour — but this is reduced by one mile an hour for every point of Load he carries. He cannot physically carry a load which inflicts a Burden more than five points greater than his Strength (i.e. 15 points of Load for a character with Strength 0, 10 points of Load for - character with Strength — 1, etc.). A second, unencumbered individual is a Load of 21 on average (see Grogs, Chapter 4).\nConcentration Duration is better than Sun Duration for this spell since in the former case the caster can end it at will, but the effect is often enchanted into an item that maintains concentration for the caster, for added safety.","source":"TME","page":111,"indexKey":"mercurys-winged-sandals","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/co.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730240398532,"modifiedTime":1730240398532,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"0WADalWs3kilFmfO","folder":"G2cgv5WjMszSYrBJ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Conjure the Mighty Barn","system":{"technique":{"value":"cr"},"form":{"value":"he"},"baseLevel":3,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"targetSize":3,"complexity":2,"ritual":true,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell creates a large barn constructed entirely of wood, including paddocks, stalls, and a loft. The barn is 100 paces long and wide, and twenty feet high. The interior’s design is determined by the caster.","source":"HP","page":122,"indexKey":"conjure-the-mighty-barn","enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/he.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266541909,"modifiedTime":1730266541909,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"0Wus7eGUZ7HCAoZd","folder":"oUunfTgpdIKsTy19","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Illusion of the Shifted Image","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"im"},"baseLevel":2,"range":{"value":"voice"},"duration":{"value":"sun"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"Makes any person or object appear to be a pace away from its actual position. The image cannot be placed in a solid object. As soon as the original or image moves, the spell ends.","source":"ArM5","page":146,"indexKey":"illusion-of-the-shifted-image","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/im.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266588755,"modifiedTime":1730266588755,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"0XOQCNU3f3mJF313","folder":"6dbqyhZVkNHEsIEk","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Arms of the Salamander","system":{"technique":{"value":"cr"},"form":{"value":"co"},"baseLevel":25,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":true,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This ritual, written on a casting tablet, instantly restores a character’s lost limb. If the character has been without the limb for more than a season, it takes him about a week to become used to its presence again (rolls that require the limb are at a —3 penalty for the week). Casting this ritual requires 6 pawns of vis. Note that, unlike The Severed Limb Made Whole, this ritual does not need the original limb. If the target is missing several limbs, the most recently detached is restored by this ritual.","source":"AtD","page":98,"indexKey":"arms-of-the-salamander","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/co.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730240398532,"modifiedTime":1730240398532,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"0bVNeQmxvKMXGHQa","folder":"G2cgv5WjMszSYrBJ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Clouds of Rain and Thunder","system":{"technique":{"value":"cr"},"form":{"value":"au"},"baseLevel":3,"range":{"value":"sight"},"duration":{"value":"conc"},"target":{"value":"group"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"Creates a small but severe rainstorm, including lightning and winds. The storm gathers and breaks in a few seconds as the caster concentrates, and dissipates with similar speed when he stops doing so.\nNote that reducing the Range for this spell makes the storm increasingly unnatural, so versions of this spell with lower Range still have the same level.","source":"ArM5","page":126,"indexKey":"clouds-of-rain-and-thunder","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/au.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730239712993,"modifiedTime":1730239814316,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"eh6ejLC7eDZ9R8Pp","_id":"0cqqnfC3cN3jt4IA","sort":3000000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Stance of the Patient Tree","system":{"technique":{"value":"mu"},"form":{"value":"co"},"baseLevel":25,"range":{"value":"personal"},"duration":{"value":"sun"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":true,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"You turn yourself into a tree about 12 feet high, with a trunk about a foot thick. You can sense only the most basic things, such as night and day, strong winds, and things that can affect a tree. You can resume human form at will, but doing so ends the spell. While in tree form, you do not heal any wounds or restore any Fatigue levels. The tree branch you use to let yourself change back determines the kind of tree the target becomes, and you cannot cast the spell without the branch.","source":"ArM5","page":131,"indexKey":"stance-of-the-patient-tree","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/co.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730240398532,"modifiedTime":1730240398532,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"0geSMmQMTVWEtjLf","folder":"G2cgv5WjMszSYrBJ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
