{"type":"spell","name":"Blessing of Artemis’ Fertility","system":{"technique":{"value":"cr"},"form":{"value":"co"},"baseLevel":20,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"year"},"target":{"value":"bound"},"complexity":0,"ritual":true,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"Increases the fertility of all within the boundary, even if they were not present at the completion of the ritual. As with the spell Artemis ’ Fertility, no other magus believes that this spell works as anything other than a giant waste of precious Creo and Corpus vis.\nAurulentus points out that at his Covenant a higher than average rate of births is apparent, but most magi believe this to be merely a fluke. Other magi theorise that the mundanes are influenced by the fact that the magi have many children, and thus also act in a promiscuous way. So far, no-one has been able to replicate the spell, although Aurulentus gives copies of the Lab Texts of the spell freely to anyone asking for them.","source":"MoH","page":21,"indexKey":"blessing-of-artemis-fertility","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/co.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730240398532,"modifiedTime":1730240398532,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"3CMqn0sfvE3Oqp9F","folder":"G2cgv5WjMszSYrBJ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Tower of Lava","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"aq"},"baseLevel":3,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"part"},"targetSize":6,"complexity":3,"ritual":true,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell sculpts a tower out of hot bubbling lava. The resulting tower is solid and rigid, but if its foundations remain in lava, then the tower will dissolve back into the bulk within a day. The Part target is required, because the spell does not use all the available lava.\nThe tower is about the same size and dimensions as the one created by the spell Conjuring the Mystic Tower (see Ars Magica Fifth Edition, page 153). A Finesse roll against an Ease Factor of 15 is required to ensure that the tower is well made; failure means that the lava takes a solid but malformed shape[].","source":"HP","page":19,"indexKey":"tower-of-lava","enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/aq.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730233430460,"modifiedTime":1730239446834,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"3G7vvaJd7LugBXFX","folder":"U1PQp4E5HVBU8pTj","sort":700000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Conflagratious Lanyard","system":{"technique":{"value":"mu"},"form":{"value":"ig"},"baseLevel":10,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moon"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":true,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This is a spell Alexander designed to avenge a personal slight. This spell transforms a large campfire into a bootlace, glove, thong, lanyard, belt, or similar leather product, for Moon Duration. When the spell’s duration expires, the campfire continues burning as a natural fire, if it has sufficient fuel and air. A person wearing the item suffers +5 Damage in the first round, and in each subsequent round provided the fire has sufficient fuel to continue burning. Alexander appears to have used this spell to burn all of his rival’s favorite clothes, by incinerating the contents of a closet. Rumors that the rival’s ship was lost at sea with all hands have never been proven.","source":"MoH","page":13,"indexKey":"conflagratious-lanyard","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/ig.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266564295,"modifiedTime":1730266564295,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"3Oy7KFDGcisq4mvn","folder":"TXWRpVwDyXc4LXyP","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
