{"type":"spell","name":"The Chirurgeon’s Healing Touch","system":{"technique":{"value":"cr"},"form":{"value":"co"},"baseLevel":15,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":true,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell heals a single Light Wound suffered by the person touched. This spell does not heal damage from poison or disease.","source":"ArM5","page":129,"indexKey":"the-chirurgeons-healing-touch","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/co.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730240398532,"modifiedTime":1730240398532,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"LpSloLkGuDSrvix4","folder":"G2cgv5WjMszSYrBJ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Hold Chur","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"co"},"baseLevel":5,"range":{"value":"voice"},"duration":{"value":"sun"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":1,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"Holds the target completely motionless for the duration of the spell. In addition, the spell closes the eyes of the target and keeps them firmly shut, so that he is unable to see for the duration of the spell.\nChur is a troublesome grog of the covenant. A lesser version of this spell was used to stop him when he was doing mischief. Aurulentus soon realized that a more- powerful version would have many uses: as a combat spell, as a spell to act without witnesses, and as a spell to stop nosy mundanes. It was once used on a friendly grog who came under the influence of a mind control spell to stop him from attacking his group without harming him.","source":"MoH","page":22,"indexKey":"hold-chur","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/co.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730240398532,"modifiedTime":1730240398532,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"Lr7RMUlh3yCTgxDz","folder":"G2cgv5WjMszSYrBJ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"A Song of All These Faerie Places","system":{"technique":{"value":"in"},"form":{"value":"vi"},"baseLevel":3,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"conc"},"target":{"value":"group"},"complexity":0,"enhancingRequisite":2,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":true,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":true,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"When the caster stands at a place where the boundary between levels of a faerie regio can be crossed easily, he is able to sing a song or play music that describes the scene on the other side of the regio boundary.\nAs the song sings of each feature on the other side of the boundary, they become clearer in the visual illusion. They then fade slightly as the song moves onto the next feature. For example, where the first line of the song describes the lush grass, in the higher level the grass becomes visible through the boundary, bright and clear. As the next line describes the dry stone wall surrounding the meadow, the wall appears in the illusion but the grass becomes more misty and distant.\nThose able to see the illusion are also able to pass through from one regio level to the next, as they can see the necessary method. If crossing the regio boundary requires other conditions (help from a resident or a particular date, for example), the spell does not work.\nAs the caster must be standing exactly at the point where the regio layers meet and form a boundary, this spell can rarely be used to actually discern the location of that boundary.","source":"MoH","page":142,"indexKey":"a-song-of-all-these-faerie-places","targetSize":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/vi.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266633698,"modifiedTime":1730266633698,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"M4nQPnxzbZMr2bcg","folder":"FLOveJlX4MXFkepb","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"That I may come unto you with joy by the will of God, and may with you be refreshed","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"co"},"baseLevel":25,"range":{"value":"personal"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"Your faith in God immediately restores a single lost Fatigue level, something impossible for Hermetic magic.","source":"CI","page":67,"indexKey":"that-i-may-come-unto-you-with-joy-by-the-will-of-god-and-may-with-you-be-refreshed","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/co.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730240398532,"modifiedTime":1730240398532,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"M6lY9naHAaaIe4h9","folder":"G2cgv5WjMszSYrBJ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Calm Mind of Resolute Behavior","system":{"technique":{"value":"pe"},"form":{"value":"me"},"baseLevel":15,"range":{"value":"personal"},"duration":{"value":"diam"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"For the duration of this spell, all emotions are banished from the caster’s mind. This makes the caster unable to feel fear, doubt, hope, or any other emotion. Any effort to manipulate the caster based on his emotions will automatically fail. The caster can make no rolls based on his Personality Traits for the duration of the spell. Despite the temporary absence of emotions, the caster’s goals and priorities remain unchanged and the caster retains recollections of emotions that he has previously felt.\nLambert’s mater believed that this spell was an essential tool for anyone who dealt with the faeries. She believed that casting Calm Mind of Resolute Behavior, to provide Lambert with a moment’s clear reflection before embarking on an activity that might be influenced by the persuasion of charismatic faeries, would save her apprentice from many unwise decisions. Lambert casts Calm Mind of Resolute Behavior when he has an important choice to make and wants to see how he would approach the problem without the complications of his emotions coloring the issue. Lambert finds casting this spell to be quite unpleasant, though, and he greatly fears the possible consequences of miscasting a Perdo Mentem spell on himself.","source":"MoH","page":62,"indexKey":"calm-mind-of-resolute-behavior","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/me.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266602531,"modifiedTime":1730266602531,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"MAL0PwhsrwIJOpu2","folder":"A2fOZ4LIRFoc2Ij8","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Cheating the Reaper","system":{"technique":{"value":"cr"},"form":{"value":"co"},"baseLevel":25,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":true,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"Resolves a major (or less severe) crisis caused by aging (see page 170). The target still requires rest for the remainder of the season to recover fully. Each application of this spell causes Warping.","source":"ArM5","page":129,"indexKey":"cheating-the-reaper","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/co.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730240398532,"modifiedTime":1730240398532,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"MFxTq5NNzqLrXXrL","folder":"G2cgv5WjMszSYrBJ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Lifting the Storm","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"au"},"baseLevel":5,"range":{"value":"voice"},"duration":{"value":"sun"},"target":{"value":"group"},"targetSize":2,"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"Poor weather can keep ships anchored in harbor for weeks, while their captains wait for the weather to turn. This spell controls even the strongest of storms, carving a channel through the weather through which ships can sail.\nNote that the spell is powerful enough to lift a storm across a harbor, but the effect is somewhat localized. This means that the weather may still be problematic out to sea, but at least the ships are able to safely leave the more treacherous inshore waters. The Sun duration allows multiple ships to sail under a single casting.","source":"HP","page":74,"indexKey":"lifting-the-storm","enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/au.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730239712993,"modifiedTime":1730239814316,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"folder":"eh6ejLC7eDZ9R8Pp","_id":"MPj9W2x8Wd85z3Ux","sort":1900000,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Nature’s Kindest Seat","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"te"},"baseLevel":3,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"sun"},"target":{"value":"group"},"complexity":1,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell conjures a group of seats from the ground, centered on the point the user touches. The number of chairs the spell produces can be controlled by the caster, summoning up to ten.\nThe chairs rise from the ground and each molds itself to the nearest person as he sits back. Each chair is always at least passably comfortable, but notably more so when cast in a meadow with lush grass. Each chair sinks slowly back into the ground, leaving no trace, as the spell nears the end of its duration. The spell only works on sand or soil, a limitation Yestin aims to fix some time in the future.\nYestin decided that, to better capture an audience and draw them into the music, there was nothing like a little peripheral magic to increase anticipation. Yestin has never been shy about using his magic.\nYestin’s sigil manifesting in this spell can occasionally take his audience by surprise, as at first nothing seems to happen ... and then the chairs spring from the ground.","source":"MoH","page":142,"indexKey":"natures-kindest-seat","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/te.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266623057,"modifiedTime":1730266623057,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"MPxBjZSxndIDMBON","folder":"Cy6JvysNx2CNSwuF","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Quiet the Cursing Tongue","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"vi"},"baseLevel":1,"range":{"value":"voice"},"duration":{"value":"sun"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"The target of this spell cannot use any curse magic with a level less than or equal to (spell level - 10). If the curse magic is controlled by a Supernatural Ability, then its level is equivalent to (Score x 5). This spell can be used as a template for spells that affect other types of exotic magic.","source":"HoH:S","page":129,"indexKey":"quiet-the-cursing-tongue","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/vi.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266633698,"modifiedTime":1730266633698,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"MUaenWuG0ZJstOPp","folder":"FLOveJlX4MXFkepb","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"The Invisible Eye Revealed","system":{"technique":{"value":"in"},"form":{"value":"vi"},"baseLevel":1,"range":{"value":"personal"},"duration":{"value":"conc"},"target":{"value":"touch"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"The caster can feel any magical means currently being used to spy on him. The representation varies in a way that depends on the spell, but it often feels like something touching the magus’s back. For example, a magus being spied upon with Enchantment of the Scrying Pool might feel wet fingers, while a magus who is being tracked by The Inexorable Search might feel a finger running over his skin. This spell detects the use of Intellego spells of up to double the level of this spell. A special spell is required because most Intellego spells are designed to be subtle, and they are more subtle at higher levels.","source":"ArM5","page":157,"indexKey":"the-invisible-eye-revealed","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/vi.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266633698,"modifiedTime":1730266633698,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"MY6SOaYx8Um3gRu6","folder":"FLOveJlX4MXFkepb","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Glass Broom","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"te"},"baseLevel":3,"range":{"value":"sight"},"duration":{"value":"conc"},"target":{"value":"group"},"complexity":1,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell moves a lot of glass objects around. The spell can be used to move around glass created by The Shattered Goblet. It can also be used to move other glass around.\nIf a Finesse Roll against an Ease Factor of 9 is failed, then the glass is broken during transit (which is not a problem if the glass is just glass shards).","source":"HP","page":89,"indexKey":"glass-broom","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/te.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266623057,"modifiedTime":1730266623057,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"MYjVS9aaDbKsfCTT","folder":"Cy6JvysNx2CNSwuF","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Bring the Herd to Market","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"an"},"baseLevel":10,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"group"},"complexity":4,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"Instantly transports a Group of standard Individuals up to seven leagues, usually to a location known to the caster. This is often sufficient to transfer a flock from its pasture to market. This spell can affect up to two hundred chickens (Size —3), fifty sheep (Size —1), ten ponies (Size +1), or five horses (Size +2).","source":"TME","page":108,"indexKey":"bring-the-herd-to-market","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"TGGoHS"},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/an.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":"Compendium.world.spells-animal.Item.MZA8D7jm0vuX6b87","duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.3","createdTime":1729689989096,"modifiedTime":1729689989096,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"MZA8D7jm0vuX6b87","ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3},"folder":"Wzb8TRtvqtVwjohA","sort":0}
{"type":"spell","name":"Links of Stone","system":{"technique":{"value":"in"},"form":{"value":"te"},"baseLevel":4,"range":{"value":"arc"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"The caster holds a piece of stone in her hands and receives a brief mental image of the surroundings of the object that this stone is an Arcane Connection to. This spell could be used to find the statue that a fragment came from, or the quarry that the blocks of a castle were chiseled from. If the stone is an Arcane Connection to several things, then the newest Arcane Connection, or the closest, is revealed.","source":"AnM","page":56,"indexKey":"links-of-stone","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/te.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266623057,"modifiedTime":1730266623057,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"MZTSyCtnclSOYJcv","folder":"Cy6JvysNx2CNSwuF","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"A Mightier Channel","system":{"technique":{"value":"pe"},"form":{"value":"te"},"baseLevel":3,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"part"},"targetSize":3,"complexity":1,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"On casting this spell while touching the river bank, the river is dredged, deepening and widening it as required by the casting magus. A single casting is enough to prepare a small waterway to take a large river barge, or a larger waterway to take a buss or cog.","source":"HP","page":57,"indexKey":"a-mightier-channel","enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/te.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266623057,"modifiedTime":1730266623057,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"MZlETfPMNOwsKWNI","folder":"Cy6JvysNx2CNSwuF","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Passage to the Place Pictured","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"co"},"baseLevel":35,"range":{"value":"personal"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":true,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell transports the caster anywhere. As part of the Ritual, the caster must paint or draw a picture of the location to which he wishes to travel. If the player succeeds in making a Dexterity + Craft roll of 9 and the spell is cast successfully, the magus is transported to the site depicted. If the roll is botched the character may be transported to the location but buried in a wall, be sent to a place that merely resembles the intended location, or be sent to a Faerie regio.\nNote: This spell is listed as a possible laboratory project that may be produced from Insights gained from researching Defixio Magic.","source":"AnM","page":45,"indexKey":"passage-to-the-place-pictured","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/co.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730240398532,"modifiedTime":1730240398532,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"Mhhp8ocKUrhuLb3Q","folder":"G2cgv5WjMszSYrBJ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Cargo of Angel’s Wings","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"te"},"baseLevel":35,"range":{"value":"arc"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"enhancingRequisite":1,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":true,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"The caster transports the target object to the location of an Arcane Connection. Hermanus used this spell to obtain vis and Arcane Connections from the location of the Wooden Mannequin that he used to explore the world without leaving his laboratory. In order to use this spell from a distance, Hermanus employed a spell similar to Opening the Intangible Tunnel (Ars Magica Fifth Edition page 162) in conjunction with the casting tablet.","source":"LH","page":119,"indexKey":"cargo-of-angels-wings","targetSize":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/te.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266623057,"modifiedTime":1730266623057,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"MisYfvLUEnDGu20p","folder":"Cy6JvysNx2CNSwuF","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Silvery Scales of the Knight","system":{"technique":{"value":"cr"},"form":{"value":"te"},"baseLevel":5,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"sun"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":2,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":true,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"Conjure a suit of full chain mail armor. The Animal requisite is required to create the armor’s leather straps, woolen padding, and gambeson — without these elements, the armor would not be effective. The styling of the armor, including any crest that appears on the helmet, depends on your Wizard’s Sigil. The armor is magical, so its wearer cannot punch or grapple a magic­resistant creature while wearing the gauntlets. The armor has the same Load as non-magical armor, and it takes just as long to put on (several minutes at least). An Intelligence + Finesse roll against an Ease Factor of 9 is required to make armor of average quality; a failed roll may result in reduced Protection and/or increased Load, at the storyguide’s discretion.","source":"HoH:S","page":37,"indexKey":"silvery-scales-of-the-knight","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/te.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266623057,"modifiedTime":1730266623057,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"Mq6J0O8MEuwUvJir","folder":"Cy6JvysNx2CNSwuF","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Wizard’s Boost (Form)","system":{"technique":{"value":"mu"},"form":{"value":"vi"},"baseLevel":1,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"You cast this spell as another spell of a level less than this one is cast. The effect of the other spell increases 5 levels in power, but not past the level of the Wizard’s Boost. The effects of the extra 5 levels of power are for the storyguide to determine. A Wizard’s Boost may never affect a single spell more than once. There are ten versions of this spell, one for each Hermetic Form. There are other versions of this spell, each of which affects one of range, duration, and target, for any Form. This does not allow spontaneous or formulaic spells to reach Year duration or Boundary Target, unless the Wizard’s Boost is a ritual.\nNote: The line in italics above was removed in the errata.","source":"ArM5","page":160,"indexKey":"wizards-boost-form","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/vi.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266633698,"modifiedTime":1730266633698,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"MqJ7x04kKxrbtIW9","folder":"FLOveJlX4MXFkepb","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Wizard’s Initiation","system":{"technique":{"value":"cr"},"form":{"value":"vi"},"baseLevel":1,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":true,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":true,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This ritual may only be cast in a consecrated temple dedicated to Mercury (see Consecration of Mercury’s House).\nThe target of this ritual gains The Gift.\nUnfortunately, this ritual does not work (see insert in Mythic Locations for details). If a character attempts to cast the ritual, then regardless of Casting Score the ritual does not work. In addition, roll an extra botch die in the case of a possible botch.\nThere is no way of discerning that the ritual does not work, other than by reading (and trusting), the Mercurian literature on the subject (see insert) or attempting to cast and failing.","source":"Mythic Locations","page":99,"indexKey":"wizards-initiation","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/vi.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266633698,"modifiedTime":1730266633698,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"MtXArLDugz1NxmhK","folder":"FLOveJlX4MXFkepb","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Remembered Messages","system":{"technique":{"value":"mu"},"form":{"value":"me"},"baseLevel":1,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"sun"},"target":{"value":"bound"},"complexity":0,"ritual":true,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"To use this spell successfully requires a little preparation, because each target needs to be prepared with a memory that can be altered with little trouble. For example, at sporting or cultural events, everyone may be asked to repeat the recipe for sea urchin soup, or memorize a string of flags.\nWhen this spell is required, the memory of the recipe is replaced with a single useful piece of information, or the flags are replaced with a single useful image. For example, an evacuation plan can be distributed in this way, or a series of mustering points for militias.\n* Remember to add further magnitudes to increase Boundary size.","source":"TME","page":74,"indexKey":"remembered-messages","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/me.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266602531,"modifiedTime":1730266602531,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"MuB9OTDBtcraGBsP","folder":"A2fOZ4LIRFoc2Ij8","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"The Factor’s Roll Call","system":{"technique":{"value":"in"},"form":{"value":"me"},"baseLevel":15,"range":{"value":"eye"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell probes the mind of the target to reveal if he has ever heard a specific word. Persephone uses this spell to determine whether a given person is one of her agents — since she operates her agents remotely she instructs her factors to say an obscure word to all recruited agents. This spell therefore tells her if a person is in her employ. She has on occasion used it to discover whether her identity has been leaked. The word she most commonly uses is “shibboleth,” although theologians may have heard this word before.","source":"MoH","page":92,"indexKey":"the-factors-roll-call","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/me.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266602531,"modifiedTime":1730266602531,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"Mv1Co6VeJ8ihEDNN","folder":"A2fOZ4LIRFoc2Ij8","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
