{"type":"spell","name":"Incantation of Summoning the Dead","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"me"},"baseLevel":15,"range":{"value":"arc"},"duration":{"value":"conc"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":true,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"Calls up a person’s ghost. You must be on the spot where the person died, or must have the corpse (either of these constitutes an Arcane Connection). Alternatively, you can summon any ghost that haunts the area you are in, if you know the ghost’s full name, according to the Law of Names. Those buried by Church ceremony and those have who gone straight to heaven (that is, saints and crusaders, as opposed to the normal folk who must wait for a time before going on) are not available for summoning. If the ghost has Magic Resistance, you must penetrate that resistance in order to summon it.","source":"ArM5","page":152,"indexKey":"incantation-of-summoning-the-dead","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/me.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266602531,"modifiedTime":1730266602531,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"YWE5pBh5lx6FzCl3","folder":"A2fOZ4LIRFoc2Ij8","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Hunt for the Wild Herb","system":{"technique":{"value":"in"},"form":{"value":"he"},"baseLevel":2,"range":{"value":"personal"},"duration":{"value":"conc"},"target":{"value":"smell"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"When you cast this spell, you can smell one sort of plant, and follow the scent, as long as you continue to concentrate. You must have a sample of the type of plant you are looking for. A Perception stress roll of 64- is needed to follow the scent. If there is no plant of the relevant type fairly close by (close enough to smell), you smell nothing, although the spell still works.","source":"ArM5","page":136,"indexKey":"hunt-for-the-wild-herb","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/he.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266541909,"modifiedTime":1730266541909,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"YaWQUZpOH3wo1JE7","folder":"oUunfTgpdIKsTy19","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Duplicate the Mechanism","system":{"technique":{"value":"cr"},"form":{"value":"te"},"baseLevel":5,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"group"},"complexity":2,"enhancingRequisite":1,"ritual":true,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":true,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell creates an exact duplicate of an existing mechanism. An armillary sphere itself is complex and fiddly, but nonmagi cal. The precision of the mechanism is limited by the precision of the duplicated source.\nStatus-conscious magi may prefer the alternative Level 45 ritual Duplicate the Noble Mechanism, which creates a precious metal (silver or gold, or both) mechanism.","source":"TMRE","page":52,"indexKey":"duplicate-the-mechanism","targetSize":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/te.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266623057,"modifiedTime":1730266623057,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"YdiSZDYmq8EXlPCc","folder":"Cy6JvysNx2CNSwuF","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"The False Dune","system":{"technique":{"value":"mu"},"form":{"value":"im"},"baseLevel":2,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"ring"},"target":{"value":"circle"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"Sometimes Alexander can’t just make an unnaturally cool, dark space, surrounded by a moat of scorpions, when he wants to camp. This spell changes the way his camp looks and sounds. He often makes it appear to be a sand dune or copse of trees.","source":"MoH","page":14,"indexKey":"the-false-dune","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/im.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266588755,"modifiedTime":1730266588755,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"YgthxYtj3sTvkDTk","folder":"6dbqyhZVkNHEsIEk","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Dance of the Spidery Ink","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"he"},"baseLevel":5,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"part"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":true,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This effect causes a small quantity of text (up to a page) to form into a spidery creature and walk from one piece of paper or vellum to another. The two pieces of paper or vellum are held in either hand of the caster. Casting the spell transfers the text to the second piece of paper or vellum.\nNote that this spell does not attempt to understand the moving text in any way. In order to preserve the sense of the text, the caster must make a Dex + Finesse roll against an Ease Factor of 9 (if he understands the text) or 12 (if he does not understand the text).\nFor this spell to work, the ink must be made of a plant product (which is common). A similar spell designed with an Animal, Corpus, or Terram Form will be needed if the ink is an animal, human, or mineral product.\nSimilar spells with longer durations and a Group target could be invented to transfer the entire text from a large work. For a Lab Text, for every magnitude of effect (level divided by 5), it takes one hour to move the text. For a summa or tractatus, it takes one hour to move the text per point of Source Quality. Note that this only moves the text from one place to another; it does not create a copy of the text.\nThe Muto requisite is required to make the ink stick to the new piece of parchment.","source":"HP","page":93,"indexKey":"dance-of-the-spidery-ink","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/he.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266541909,"modifiedTime":1730266541909,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"YiyMP3K4woaeM09Z","folder":"oUunfTgpdIKsTy19","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Retreat Into the Shell of Shadow","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"co"},"baseLevel":15,"range":{"value":"personal"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"The caster instantly transports himself to any location he can see, not more than 50 paces distant. A puff of black, quickly dis solving vapor is all that is left behind once the caster vanishes and reappears at the destination. If the initial point or endpoint of the leap is Warded, or if the caster’s magic is resisted, that resistance must be overcome much the same as when targeting a Warded area (see Aegis of the Hearth, Ars Magica Fifth Edition, page 161). Tolides developed this spell to retreat into the shadow of a dark corner. If the endpoint of the transportation is exposed to unclouded daylight, Tolides must make a Concentration roll against an Ease Factor of 9 to gracefully reach his destination. A failure usually means that he tumbles and falls, is disorientated, or is enfeebled, whereas a botch calls for more-dramatic results to reflect his malediction. Note that this quirk is not a flaw of the spell, but an effect of Tolides’ Susceptibility to Sunlight.","source":"MoH","page":131,"indexKey":"retreat-into-the-shell-of-shadow","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/co.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730240398532,"modifiedTime":1730240398532,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"YlMdzBb4aqFFuUFX","folder":"G2cgv5WjMszSYrBJ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"The Instant Ring Fort","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"te"},"baseLevel":3,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"part"},"targetSize":1,"complexity":1,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"Earth and stone is excavated from a circular ditch around the caster to create a circle of packed earth and rock four paces in diameter, two paces thick, and eight feet high. The spell does not break stone, so any boulders that extend beyond the target are left in place. The ring fort provides an excellent defensive position for holding off a superior enemy, or providing cover for or from archers.","source":"MoH","page":50,"indexKey":"the-instant-ring-fort","enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/te.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266623057,"modifiedTime":1730266623057,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"YmuMVMYuadBwYUf2","folder":"Cy6JvysNx2CNSwuF","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Sever the Unwanted Limb","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"co"},"baseLevel":20,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"One of the target’s limbs is amputated cleanly and painlessly, without bleeding. The amputation requires an Intelligence + Finesse roll against an Ease Factor of 12; failure indicates that the target is left intact. If this roll succeeds, the target acquires the Lame or Missing Hand Flaw. If used instead of surgical intervention, the patient’s failed Recovery roll is treated as a stable result instead.","source":"A&A","page":60,"indexKey":"sever-the-unwanted-limb","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/co.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730240398532,"modifiedTime":1730240398532,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"YoJnUJBusgXvDfty","folder":"G2cgv5WjMszSYrBJ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"The Unseen Shipwright","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"he"},"baseLevel":5,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"group"},"targetSize":1,"complexity":1,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":true,"vi":false},"description":"The magus selects a pile of wood and formed iron fixtures, and the spell cuts, carves, and joins the wood into the hull of a target ship, repairing splits and holes under the magus’ direction. The worst damage is repaired first so that the vessel is always left seaworthy and the repairs are practically seamless.\nA Perception + Finesse roll is required against an Ease Factor set by the storyguide. The table on Covenants, page 49, is a useful guide, but a rule of thumb is that repairing a small leak or a splintered rudder is a task of average difficulty taking no more than a day for an Ease Factor of 12, while refloating a wrecked ship is almost impossible, with an Ease Factor of at least 27 (plus any modifiers that the storyguide imposes based on how long it might take a mundane shipwright to refloat the vessel). The magus must have appropriate materials to hand in order to make repairs.","source":"HP","page":64,"indexKey":"the-unseen-shipwright","enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/he.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266541909,"modifiedTime":1730266541909,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"Z3bOPOkikHj04Hnd","folder":"oUunfTgpdIKsTy19","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"The Maculate Noblewoman","system":{"technique":{"value":"in"},"form":{"value":"co"},"baseLevel":10,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"Accurately determines the underlying reason for the infertility of the target.\nAurulentus successfully used this spell to compare two groups: those infertile from natural causes and those rendered infertile by a Longevity Ritual. Exploring the fundamental differences between these two groups, he was able to gather further insights for his breakthrough.","source":"MoH","page":21,"indexKey":"the-maculate-noblewoman","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/co.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730240398532,"modifiedTime":1730240398532,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"Z4Hi2cq846NHt2ZW","folder":"G2cgv5WjMszSYrBJ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Conjuring the Magical Wolf","system":{"technique":{"value":"cr"},"form":{"value":"an"},"baseLevel":50,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"enhancingRequisite":1,"ritual":true,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":true,"te":false,"vi":true},"description":"This ritual spell creates a magical wolf, as described in Ars Magica Fifth Edition, page 193. Once created, the wolf is not naturally friendly with the caster, and instantly reacts according to its own motivations.","source":"HP","page":126,"indexKey":"conjuring-the-magical-wolf","targetSize":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"TGGoHS"},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/an.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":"Compendium.world.spells-animal.Item.Z4vWtXPeOWn1RRtr","duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.3","createdTime":1729689989096,"modifiedTime":1729689989096,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"Z4vWtXPeOWn1RRtr","ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3},"folder":"Wzb8TRtvqtVwjohA","sort":0}
{"type":"spell","name":"The Curse of Diana","system":{"technique":{"value":"pe"},"form":{"value":"an"},"baseLevel":3,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell causes an animal of Size +1 or smaller to lose all its fur. Several members of House Jerbiton find hairless cats beautiful, but their opinion is not shared by many.","source":"App","page":45,"indexKey":"the-curse-of-diana","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"reviewed","reviewer":"TGGoHS"},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/an.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":"Compendium.world.spells-animal.Item.ZCS62zMG7QnGkHmP","duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.3","createdTime":1729689989096,"modifiedTime":1729689989096,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"ZCS62zMG7QnGkHmP","ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3},"folder":"Wzb8TRtvqtVwjohA","sort":0}
{"type":"spell","name":"Object of Increased Size","system":{"technique":{"value":"mu"},"form":{"value":"te"},"baseLevel":4,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"sun"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":1,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell enlarges an inanimate object originally no bigger than a large chest. The object doubles in each dimension and increases its weight eight times. The size increase is based on the object’s original, natural size, so casting the spell more than once on an object has no effect. Noble elements like gold, silver, and gems, are not affected by this spell. If any part of the item resists growth, the item as a whole does not grow. Casting requisites are required for the appropriate Form for the target.","source":"ArM5","page":154,"indexKey":"object-of-increased-size","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/te.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266623057,"modifiedTime":1730266623057,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"ZFqMytogo9qwUidV","folder":"Cy6JvysNx2CNSwuF","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Heal Thy Broken Voice","system":{"technique":{"value":"cr"},"form":{"value":"he"},"baseLevel":15,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":true,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This ritual spell mends a damaged wooden musical instrument. The instrument is returned to the peak of its former condition; that is, the height of its playing life after the instrument had matured and settled, and before decay or accident had affected it. The instrument is also cleaned of all dirt by this spell, as that helps bring it closer to its ideal.\nInstruments that have more than one part, such as a fiddle and its original bow, are treated as the same item and are both repaired so long as all parts are present at the ritual’s casting.\nA badly made instrument cannot be repaired beyond the height of its playing life, so it retains any flaws it had before it was damaged. An enchanted instrument can be made whole again, but any magical enchantments lost as a result of damage are not restored.\nThis spell has a base level of 15 by analogy with the Creo Corpus guidelines, allowing the healing of “light” damage. Casting requisites are needed for instruments with any non-Herbam components (cat-gut, horse hair, metal pins, etc.).","source":"MoH","page":139,"indexKey":"heal-thy-broken-voice","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/he.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266541909,"modifiedTime":1730266541909,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"ZFtV47P01m8sqHhD","folder":"oUunfTgpdIKsTy19","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Sense the True Path","system":{"technique":{"value":"in"},"form":{"value":"te"},"baseLevel":2,"range":{"value":"arc"},"duration":{"value":"conc"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"Requires Boosted and Tethered Magic or Mutantum Magic.\nYou can sense the direction of any location to which you have an Arcane Connection. You feel an instinctive pull towards its relative position to you while you concentrate, though you must make simple Perception rolls of 6+ to stay on track when traveling on foot through woods or brush, and if your destination moves, the Ease Factor of this roll increases depending on its speed.\nThe spell is tethered, so that it may be controlled by another, and boosted so that it may be made to last longer if necessary.","source":"HoH:TL","page":102,"indexKey":"sense-the-true-path","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/te.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266623057,"modifiedTime":1730266623057,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"ZKJc16LEpQ7cLoRR","folder":"Cy6JvysNx2CNSwuF","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
