{"type":"spell","name":"Close the Black Gate","system":{"technique":{"value":"pe"},"form":{"value":"co"},"baseLevel":5,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell destroys a corpse, turning it into a black pool of sticky, viscous liquid. This effect can be used to stop the sodales of a Wizard’s War victim from using a Whispers Through the Black Gate to ask his ghost how he was attacked.\nObviously, there are other techniques for communicating with a ghost. However, Whispers Through the Black Gate is the most common such spell in use in the Order.","source":"HP","page":85,"indexKey":"close-the-black-gate","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/co.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730240398532,"modifiedTime":1730240398532,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"ZLxBsgc4O14yWeL1","folder":"G2cgv5WjMszSYrBJ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Dancing Mania","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"me"},"baseLevel":15,"range":{"value":"voice"},"duration":{"value":"conc"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"The target of the spell dances in a wild and ecstatic way for as long as the caster concentrates. The target dances so fast and wildly that he must make a Stamina roll against an Ease Factor of 6 every round to avoid losing a Fatigue level.","source":"MoH","page":126,"indexKey":"dancing-mania","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/me.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266602531,"modifiedTime":1730266602531,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"ZNsppXWcUkz9Ktc6","folder":"A2fOZ4LIRFoc2Ij8","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Discourse of Glowing Tongues","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"ig"},"baseLevel":4,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"conc"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell controls the sounds created by a fire to make them form words. The alteration is subtle; words are formed of the natural roar, crackles, and hisses of the fire — not with any additional sound. Someone listening at the fire who knows to expect the words can make them out with a Perception + Awareness roll against an Ease Factor of 3. A character who is not aware that the fire is speaking needs to roll against an Ease Factor of 9 on a Perception + Awareness test to realize that the fire is making words at all.\nRanulf and his apprentice (who is also quite talented with the Art of Ignem) use this spell to target fires that are subject to the Unified Flame spell. Because the Unified Flame is cast by Ranulf within his covenant, the communication is not impeded by his covenant’s Aegis of the Hearth. Neither Ranulf nor his apprentice knows Discourse of Glowing Tongues as a formulaic spell; instead, they cast it spontaneously when needed. Note that this spell has a Range of Touch and may be difficult or even damaging to cast on a particularly hot fire.","source":"MoH","page":111,"indexKey":"discourse-of-glowing-tongues","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/ig.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266564295,"modifiedTime":1730266564295,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"ZPI6JH3EarGyY54M","folder":"TXWRpVwDyXc4LXyP","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Traveler’s Respite","system":{"technique":{"value":"cr"},"form":{"value":"co"},"baseLevel":15,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"group"},"complexity":0,"ritual":true,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This ritual spell restores one Long-Term Fatigue level to up to 10 individuals. Note that as this is a Ritual spell, the caster will lose at least one Long-Term Fatigue level himself, and possibly more if his Casting Total is low (see Ars Magica Fifth Edition page 81).\nNote: This spell is listed as a possible laboratory project that may be produced from Insights gained from researching Folk Witch magic.","source":"HMRE","page":51,"indexKey":"travelers-respite","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/co.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730240398532,"modifiedTime":1730240398532,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"ZT3s7rHJsUbEYJTd","folder":"G2cgv5WjMszSYrBJ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Imprison a Ghost in a Vessel","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"me"},"baseLevel":5,"range":{"value":"voice"},"duration":{"value":"sun"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":0,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell forces a ghost into a container of some type. The spirit remains bound within the vessel for the duration of the spell. While the spirit cannot affect its prison with magic to force its release, its powers are not otherwise limited.","source":"HP","page":97,"indexKey":"imprison-a-ghost-in-a-vessel","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/me.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266602531,"modifiedTime":1730266602531,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"ZVctX2X9wbQ7R1CZ","folder":"A2fOZ4LIRFoc2Ij8","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
{"type":"spell","name":"Scattering Like Light","system":{"technique":{"value":"mu"},"form":{"value":"te"},"baseLevel":5,"range":{"value":"voice"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":2,"enhancingRequisite":1,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":true,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"This spell changes the metal in an object, a sword for example, into iconic species. Passing light carries off these species, which are absorbed when they strike a non- reflective surface. This spell disintegrates objects, so it has obvious combat advantages, but it was originally created by an artist seeking an efficient method of plating objects in metal. He placed the metal and the object he wanted to plate, levitating, in a supernaturally lit box, mirrored on the inside, and used this spell to turn the metal first into species, then back again. This created a smooth coat of metal around the object, and the interior of the box.","source":"HoH:S","page":63,"indexKey":"scattering-like-light","targetSize":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/te.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266623057,"modifiedTime":1730266623057,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"ZYTa9wmfxfOveqD3","folder":"Cy6JvysNx2CNSwuF","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
