{"type":"spell","name":"Mend Thy Broken Strings","system":{"technique":{"value":"re"},"form":{"value":"he"},"baseLevel":5,"range":{"value":"touch"},"duration":{"value":"moment"},"target":{"value":"ind"},"complexity":2,"ritual":false,"technique-req":{"cr":false,"in":false,"mu":false,"pe":false,"re":false},"form-req":{"an":false,"aq":false,"au":false,"co":false,"he":false,"ig":false,"im":false,"me":false,"te":false,"vi":false},"description":"With all the required parts and/or materials of a musical instrument present, the caster uses Rego magic to repair it, including re-stringing, straightening warped wood, or any other fix that could be applied by a craftsman. The spell cannot repair splintered or broken wood, but it can reassemble or replace old parts if new materials are available. The spell cannot create any required materials that are not present.\nThis spell uses the Rego Craft Magic rules from Covenants, page 49, and so the results of the spell depend on the magus’s Finesse as described in the table.\nCasting requisites are required for non-Herbam components.","source":"MoH","page":139,"indexKey":"mend-thy-broken-strings","targetSize":0,"enhancingRequisite":0,"general":false,"levelOffset":0,"baseEffectDescription":"","applyFocus":false,"bonus":0,"bonusDesc":"","xp":0,"masteryAbilities":"","review_status":"toReview","reviewer":"","ownership":null},"img":"systems/arm5e/assets/magic/he.png","effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"12.331","systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.3.2.5","createdTime":1730266541909,"modifiedTime":1730266541909,"lastModifiedBy":"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J"},"_id":"ZlFyVlGXtJGeMQ3V","folder":"oUunfTgpdIKsTy19","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"6SdI10VpXHcBvx2J":3}}
